WEBVTT

1
00:02:18.972 --> 00:02:20.407
It's been near six years

2
00:02:20.431 --> 00:02:22.852
since I last saw
my lord husband. Maester.

3
00:02:23.602 --> 00:02:27.565
I must know... will he live?

4
00:02:27.648 --> 00:02:30.066
He led his sailors
into an ambush.

5
00:02:30.149 --> 00:02:34.238
A ship made to look
as if it were abandoned.

6
00:02:34.321 --> 00:02:38.741
In the fighting.
his neck was slashed by a corsair's dagger.

7
00:02:38.825 --> 00:02:41.370
He fell overboard into the sea.

8
00:02:41.453 --> 00:02:43.413
The wound was severe.

9
00:02:43.496 --> 00:02:45.124
Much blood was lost.

10
00:02:45.206 --> 00:02:48.085
But the greater concern
is the fever that followed.

11
00:02:48.168 --> 00:02:52.089
The ship's maester said
he burns from within.

12
00:03:04.518 --> 00:03:06.270
The ravens came in from?

13
00:03:06.352 --> 00:03:08.521
Even fall. Princess.

14
00:03:09.315 --> 00:03:11.191
So they arrive in three days.

15
00:03:14.360 --> 00:03:16.441
Let all be made ready
to receive him. Maester Kelvyn.

16
00:03:23.662 --> 00:03:24.787
The Sea Snake is strong.

17
00:03:24.871 --> 00:03:26.539
No doubt.

18
00:03:26.624 --> 00:03:31.461
And yet. I have seen
blood fever overcome men half his age.

19
00:03:31.544 --> 00:03:34.673
I will not suffer the talk
of crows in my house. Vaemond.

20
00:03:34.757 --> 00:03:37.425
I love my brother...

21
00:03:37.508 --> 00:03:40.137
but we must be honest
with ourselves.

22
00:03:40.220 --> 00:03:42.305
We may greet his ship
to find him gone.

23
00:03:42.388 --> 00:03:44.974
And who will take
the Driftwood Throne?

24
00:03:45.059 --> 00:03:46.779
My grandmother seems
quite comfortable here.

25
00:03:46.852 --> 00:03:50.980
She presides
only in the absence of her husband.

26
00:03:51.065 --> 00:03:52.733
On his death. the seat passes.

27
00:03:52.816 --> 00:03:54.859
To Lucerys Velaryon.

28
00:03:54.943 --> 00:03:56.527
As is my lord husband's desire.

29
00:03:56.612 --> 00:03:59.989
I am the Sea Snake's own blood.

30
00:04:00.073 --> 00:04:02.700
the closest kin he has left.

31
00:04:02.785 --> 00:04:04.036
Be careful. good-brother.

32
00:04:04.119 --> 00:04:06.830
One could take
your words for treason.

33
00:04:15.714 --> 00:04:18.549
I speak the truth. Rhaenys.

34
00:04:19.717 --> 00:04:22.262
And you know it.

35
00:04:22.346 --> 00:04:24.013
The matter has been decided.

36
00:04:24.097 --> 00:04:25.240
By a man whose ambition

37
00:04:25.264 --> 00:04:29.769
has brought down on us
calamity after calamity.

38
00:04:29.853 --> 00:04:33.065
My brother cares only
for the history books.

39
00:04:35.192 --> 00:04:37.485
But what of the Velaryon line?

40
00:04:37.568 --> 00:04:39.196
Is it to be snuffed out.

41
00:04:39.279 --> 00:04:43.199
supplanted by the pups
of House Strong?

42
00:04:43.282 --> 00:04:46.035
Driftmark is mine by all rights.

43
00:04:46.119 --> 00:04:48.830
And while I should
like your support.

44
00:04:48.914 --> 00:04:52.001
I do not... need it.

45
00:04:54.210 --> 00:04:57.047
The winds have shifted.

46
00:04:57.131 --> 00:05:01.385
The crown has good reason...
to take my side.

47
00:05:01.467 --> 00:05:04.345
My cousin the King would
have your tongue for this.

48
00:05:04.429 --> 00:05:09.225
But it's not a king who sits
the Iron Throne these days. good-sister.

49
00:05:10.268 --> 00:05:11.854
It's a queen.

50
00:07:30.325 --> 00:07:31.034
The Conqueror and his sisters

51
00:07:31.117 --> 00:07:34.037
sailed with a great army.

52
00:07:34.121 --> 00:07:36.265
Se Blakuata Rasho

53
00:07:36.289 --> 00:07:39.333
dranot vilinio viartis.

54
00:07:39.417 --> 00:07:43.547
And
landed at the Blackwater Rush.

55
00:07:43.630 --> 00:07:44.672
Dr a not.

56
00:07:45.965 --> 00:07:48.510
Dr a not.
Dr a not.

57
00:07:48.593 --> 00:07:50.636
Dr a not.
At the end?

58
00:07:50.720 --> 00:07:55.266
- The mouth.
- Mouth! Ah. come on. Jace. you knew that.

59
00:07:55.975 --> 00:07:58.561
Dr a not.
Dr a not.

60
00:07:58.645 --> 00:08:01.814
- Dr a not vilinio viartis.
- Dr a not.

61
00:08:02.566 --> 00:08:04.859
Dr a not.
Come on. Jace.

62
00:08:04.943 --> 00:08:06.462
Perhaps that's enough
for this morning.

63
00:08:06.486 --> 00:08:08.487
No. no.
I-I want to keep going.

64
00:08:09.948 --> 00:08:13.577
- Maester.
- Guesi misenakson Aegon undas.

65
00:08:13.660 --> 00:08:18.874
Aegon... ordered
that the trees should be...

66
00:08:18.957 --> 00:08:19.975
- ...killed.
- Felled.

67
00:08:19.999 --> 00:08:21.876
It is a related word.

68
00:08:21.960 --> 00:08:25.380
I don't expect you
to learn High Valyrian in a day. Jace.

69
00:08:25.463 --> 00:08:28.758
A king should honor
the traditions of his forbears.

70
00:08:28.842 --> 00:08:31.136
Well... unless you're planning

71
00:08:31.220 --> 00:08:32.679
to depose your own mother.

72
00:08:32.763 --> 00:08:35.015
you have plenty
of time to study.

73
00:08:42.813 --> 00:08:43.857
Leave us.

74
00:08:45.025 --> 00:08:47.652
Joffrey... come.

75
00:09:08.549 --> 00:09:11.842
He means to call
into question Luke's legitimacy.

76
00:09:12.678 --> 00:09:13.678
And by extension Jace.

77
00:09:13.719 --> 00:09:16.682
and by extension
my own claim to the throne.

78
00:09:16.765 --> 00:09:18.725
Vaemond cares only
about Driftmark

79
00:09:18.809 --> 00:09:20.935
and the Velaryon line.

80
00:09:21.019 --> 00:09:23.355
Not about our politics.

81
00:09:23.438 --> 00:09:25.482
Has he made common cause
with Otto High tower yet?

82
00:09:25.564 --> 00:09:27.317
Hm. this is what I fear.

83
00:09:27.400 --> 00:09:28.651
Rhaenys has flown to court.

84
00:09:28.735 --> 00:09:31.862
- Surely. she cannot be planning to back him.
- No.

85
00:09:31.947 --> 00:09:33.216
Whatever disagreements
we may have had.

86
00:09:33.240 --> 00:09:34.491
she's not cruel...

87
00:09:34.573 --> 00:09:38.203
- or stupid enough to do that.
- Disagreements?

88
00:09:38.286 --> 00:09:41.372
She believes we had her son
killed so that we might marry.

89
00:09:41.456 --> 00:09:45.168
Yes... and yet.
she's taken Baela to ward.

90
00:09:45.251 --> 00:09:48.005
Yes. It is Laena's
memory she honors. She has no love for us.

91
00:09:49.798 --> 00:09:52.092
Has the vipers' venom
spread so far?

92
00:09:52.174 --> 00:09:55.219
Those vipers rule
in my father's name.

93
00:09:55.304 --> 00:09:56.929
And my father...

94
00:10:03.937 --> 00:10:05.813
What choice do I have?

95
00:10:12.112 --> 00:10:13.947
To King's Landing. then.

96
00:10:54.655 --> 00:10:57.741
All hail
Rhaenyra of House Targaryen.

97
00:10:57.823 --> 00:10:59.676
Princess of Dragons tone
and heir to the Iron Throne

98
00:10:59.700 --> 00:11:04.081
and her royal consort.
Prince Daemon Targaryen.

99
00:11:37.988 --> 00:11:40.074
Welcome back. Princess.

100
00:11:40.574 --> 00:11:42.202
Lord Caswell.

101
00:11:51.794 --> 00:11:53.087
I would say it's
nice to be home.

102
00:11:53.170 --> 00:11:56.424
- but I scarcely recognize it.
- Mm.

103
00:12:00.594 --> 00:12:05.851
We have continued
to enjoy improved customs duties

104
00:12:05.934 --> 00:12:08.310
since the settling
of the Step stones.

105
00:12:08.395 --> 00:12:11.398
And the extent to
which we exploit those

106
00:12:11.481 --> 00:12:15.693
is contingent on
the harbor master's receipts.

107
00:12:15.776 --> 00:12:20.866
Of which. um. uh.
the. uh. septons have requested

108
00:12:20.948 --> 00:12:23.325
half that again
for a bronze bust

109
00:12:23.410 --> 00:12:24.743
they wish to co... to commission

110
00:12:24.828 --> 00:12:27.079
for the. the Festival
of the Mother.

111
00:12:27.164 --> 00:12:28.582
which I would not recommend.

112
00:12:28.664 --> 00:12:31.459
Thank you for that exhaustive
accounting. Lord Beesbury.

113
00:12:31.543 --> 00:12:34.587
I remind you...

114
00:12:40.342 --> 00:12:42.429
Your guests have arrived.
Your Grace.

115
00:12:42.511 --> 00:12:44.406
I trust they've been welcomed
as befits their station.

116
00:12:44.430 --> 00:12:47.350
As you instructed. Lord Hand.

117
00:12:48.934 --> 00:12:50.413
It was
my understanding Lord Corlys wished

118
00:12:50.437 --> 00:12:52.731
for his grandson Lucerys

119
00:12:52.813 --> 00:12:54.690
to succeed him
as Lord of the Tides.

120
00:12:54.774 --> 00:12:57.861
The boy has been raised
most of his life away from Driftmark.

121
00:12:57.943 --> 00:13:02.156
He can fly a dragon. yes.
but can he command a fleet?

122
00:13:02.240 --> 00:13:04.617
Ability does not
alter his claim.

123
00:13:04.700 --> 00:13:07.578
The Sea Snake has never
formally named him as heir.

124
00:13:07.661 --> 00:13:09.039
if it comes to that.

125
00:13:09.121 --> 00:13:11.708
The crown must choose
what is best for the realm.

126
00:13:11.790 --> 00:13:14.376
He is Laenor's son.
What grounds could there be...

127
00:13:14.461 --> 00:13:16.587
What indeed. Lord Beesbury.

128
00:13:16.670 --> 00:13:19.299
What indeed.

129
00:13:19.381 --> 00:13:20.568
We shall hear
Princess Rhaenyra's petition.

130
00:13:20.592 --> 00:13:22.968
along with those
of the other claimants on the morrow.

131
00:13:23.053 --> 00:13:26.055
- But...
- I do beg your pardon. my lords.

132
00:13:26.139 --> 00:13:27.557
I must greet our guests.

133
00:13:32.895 --> 00:13:35.774
Shall we levy a tax
on the sale of new wool?

134
00:13:35.857 --> 00:13:36.775
Your Grace...

135
00:13:36.857 --> 00:13:39.653
a matter has arisen that
requires your attention.

136
00:13:39.736 --> 00:13:41.862
Whatever it is. Ser Arryk.
it'll need to wait.

137
00:13:41.947 --> 00:13:45.741
- I'm Erryk. Your Grace.
- Of course. My apologies. ser.

138
00:13:45.824 --> 00:13:47.493
It's about the Prince.

139
00:13:47.577 --> 00:13:50.579
There's been
a delicate situation in his apartments.

140
00:14:22.112 --> 00:14:23.988
Father?

141
00:14:47.886 --> 00:14:51.600
- Who goes there?
- Father.

142
00:14:52.809 --> 00:14:55.437
It's me. my King.

143
00:14:56.228 --> 00:14:59.274
Rhaenyra.

144
00:14:59.607 --> 00:15:00.900
Oh...

145
00:15:01.275 --> 00:15:03.402
Oh.

146
00:15:05.822 --> 00:15:08.241
I'm here with Daemon.

147
00:15:08.324 --> 00:15:09.909
Daemon?

148
00:15:10.577 --> 00:15:11.493
Daemon?

149
00:15:11.578 --> 00:15:15.707
Daemon.

150
00:15:19.044 --> 00:15:20.337
Help me up.

151
00:15:26.675 --> 00:15:28.761
Oh...

152
00:15:37.562 --> 00:15:38.896
It has been so long.

153
00:15:44.443 --> 00:15:49.240
The Sea Snake has taken
a grave wound in battle in the Step stones.

154
00:15:50.699 --> 00:15:51.534
When?

155
00:15:51.617 --> 00:15:54.078
We won that war years ago.

156
00:15:54.161 --> 00:15:55.954
No.

157
00:15:57.457 --> 00:15:59.333
The Triarchy is resurgent.

158
00:16:00.584 --> 00:16:02.379
The fighting is anew.

159
00:16:02.462 --> 00:16:07.217
And there is a p... There is a petition to
decide upon the succession of Driftmark

160
00:16:07.299 --> 00:16:09.343
and the heir
to the Driftwood Throne.

161
00:16:12.222 --> 00:16:14.140
Petitions?

162
00:16:15.975 --> 00:16:20.230
Alicent and Otto...
they see to all that business now.

163
00:16:20.313 --> 00:16:23.065
No. brother. listen to me.

164
00:16:23.149 --> 00:16:26.568
You are to affirm
your position for Lucerys

165
00:16:26.652 --> 00:16:28.237
to be Corlys Velaryon's
successor.

166
00:16:31.073 --> 00:16:34.202
Has something happened
to Lord Corlys?

167
00:16:35.911 --> 00:16:37.746
Father...

168
00:16:37.831 --> 00:16:40.791
there's someone we wish
to introduce you to.

169
00:16:58.392 --> 00:17:01.438
Daemon.

170
00:17:01.855 --> 00:17:04.440
Brother.

171
00:17:05.525 --> 00:17:07.151
Who is that?

172
00:17:09.154 --> 00:17:10.780
Father...

173
00:17:11.990 --> 00:17:14.575
this is Aegon.

174
00:17:15.075 --> 00:17:16.618
Aegon.

175
00:17:16.703 --> 00:17:20.582
And this... is Viserys.

176
00:17:21.665 --> 00:17:25.002
Ah... Viserys.

177
00:17:27.713 --> 00:17:29.174
Oh.

178
00:17:29.256 --> 00:17:33.762
Now that is a name fit for a king.

179
00:17:37.724 --> 00:17:39.183
Oh...

180
00:17:41.518 --> 00:17:44.480
Oh. oh...

181
00:17:44.563 --> 00:17:45.814
Oh. I'm sorry.

182
00:17:46.565 --> 00:17:49.651
Oh. I'm sorry. I-I'm sorry.

183
00:17:49.736 --> 00:17:52.697
I'm so...

184
00:17:54.908 --> 00:17:57.701
Oh. I'm sorry. I'm sor...

185
00:17:57.785 --> 00:17:58.995
Please.

186
00:18:00.412 --> 00:18:03.999
- My tea... My tea.
- What tea? This?

187
00:18:04.083 --> 00:18:06.503
Yes. Yes.

188
00:18:07.920 --> 00:18:09.088
Yes.

189
00:18:36.908 --> 00:18:40.410
I brought her here immediately.

190
00:18:40.495 --> 00:18:42.412
She's seen no one else.
Your Grace.

191
00:18:47.459 --> 00:18:49.336
Come here. sweetling.

192
00:18:58.888 --> 00:19:00.139
Tell me your name.

193
00:19:03.685 --> 00:19:09.064
It's Dyana. Your Grace.
If... i-if it please you.

194
00:19:10.941 --> 00:19:14.070
Dyana. What a pretty name.

195
00:19:17.156 --> 00:19:19.158
I understand you've found
yourself in some trouble.

196
00:19:21.995 --> 00:19:24.706
I was fetching
the Prince his wine.

197
00:19:24.788 --> 00:19:28.750
and I put it on his table.
and when I turned...

198
00:19:29.334 --> 00:19:31.169
I didn't see him.

199
00:19:32.213 --> 00:19:33.590
I asked him to stop. Your Grace.

200
00:19:33.672 --> 00:19:37.342
I did. truly...

201
00:19:37.427 --> 00:19:39.429
you must believe me.

202
00:19:48.062 --> 00:19:49.605
Shh.

203
00:19:53.317 --> 00:19:55.194
Thank you for telling me. Dyana.

204
00:20:00.490 --> 00:20:02.701
- I know it wasn't your fault.
- Hm?

205
00:20:04.871 --> 00:20:06.663
I believe you.

206
00:20:06.747 --> 00:20:08.333
Y-You do?

207
00:20:09.542 --> 00:20:10.793
I do.

208
00:20:13.795 --> 00:20:15.923
But what I worry about...

209
00:20:17.007 --> 00:20:18.168
is what others might believe.

210
00:20:20.218 --> 00:20:23.514
You were alone with the Prince.
were you not?

211
00:20:23.598 --> 00:20:25.766
Yes. I...

212
00:20:25.850 --> 00:20:29.437
And no one else
saw what happened between the two of you.

213
00:20:29.519 --> 00:20:31.648
If anyone else were
to hear about this...

214
00:20:31.730 --> 00:20:36.819
- I haven't told anyone.
- You told Ser Erryk and Talya and now me.

215
00:20:36.902 --> 00:20:38.213
And though I believe
you are not to blame.

216
00:20:38.237 --> 00:20:41.615
others might not be so trusting.

217
00:20:41.698 --> 00:20:45.661
They might think you were trying
to besmirch the Prince. or worse...

218
00:20:45.745 --> 00:20:48.745
that you're the sort of girl that might
have enticed him in the first place.

219
00:20:50.291 --> 00:20:52.543
And you know what happens
to girls like that.

220
00:20:54.629 --> 00:20:58.256
I. I wouldn't dream of breathing
another word to anyone. Your Grace.

221
00:21:00.176 --> 00:21:01.718
I. I swear it on my life.

222
00:21:09.811 --> 00:21:11.437
I know you won't.

223
00:21:24.367 --> 00:21:25.868
For your troubles.

224
00:21:33.458 --> 00:21:35.294
The tea. Your Grace.

225
00:21:48.975 --> 00:21:51.143
It's best to be certain.

226
00:22:18.004 --> 00:22:20.422
Get up.

227
00:22:20.506 --> 00:22:22.132
Aegon!

228
00:22:24.802 --> 00:22:26.094
Get up!

229
00:22:26.845 --> 00:22:30.640
Mother?

230
00:22:31.641 --> 00:22:35.813
- What is it?
- "What is it? What is it?"

231
00:22:35.897 --> 00:22:37.790
What is it?"
That's all you can say for yourself?

232
00:22:37.814 --> 00:22:40.067
Has something happened?

233
00:22:40.150 --> 00:22:42.778
- Dyana.
- Mm?

234
00:22:42.862 --> 00:22:45.073
The serving girl.

235
00:22:45.156 --> 00:22:48.242
Oh. for the gods' sake.

236
00:22:48.325 --> 00:22:50.678
The girl. Aegon.
The one you sent fleeing from your company.

237
00:22:50.702 --> 00:22:53.288
Oh. it was just harmless fun.

238
00:22:53.371 --> 00:22:56.958
She didn't need to go
and get upset about it.

239
00:22:57.043 --> 00:23:01.171
Think of the shame
on your wife. on me.

240
00:23:01.255 --> 00:23:03.632
How can you keep
carrying on like this.

241
00:23:03.716 --> 00:23:05.634
especially on a day like today?

242
00:23:05.717 --> 00:23:08.720
Why? What is it today?

243
00:23:22.067 --> 00:23:23.945
You are no son of mine.

244
00:23:28.990 --> 00:23:31.326
I did not ask for this.

245
00:23:31.410 --> 00:23:34.287
I've done everything
you've asked me to.

246
00:23:34.371 --> 00:23:36.498
and I try so...

247
00:23:36.582 --> 00:23:39.919
I try so hard. but it will never
be enough for you or father.

248
00:23:42.255 --> 00:23:46.217
Have you seen Dyana?
She's supposed to dress the children.

249
00:23:53.474 --> 00:23:55.642
He looks like
a different person.

250
00:23:55.726 --> 00:24:00.148
I believe we should also
consult Maester Gerardys.

251
00:24:00.230 --> 00:24:03.025
Perhaps if he could see the
King. he'd suggest a different...

252
00:24:03.109 --> 00:24:05.111
Princess Rhaenyra.

253
00:24:05.194 --> 00:24:06.862
- And Prince Daemon.
- Hm.

254
00:24:09.323 --> 00:24:12.660
It has been so long since we were
granted the joy of your presence.

255
00:24:15.580 --> 00:24:17.122
Indeed. Your Grace.

256
00:24:17.206 --> 00:24:20.543
Though not long enough
to merit a greeting upon our arrival.

257
00:24:20.625 --> 00:24:23.545
I'm sure the Queen
had pressing business. my love.

258
00:24:23.629 --> 00:24:26.966
What can either of us
know of ruling a kingdom?

259
00:24:27.048 --> 00:24:28.842
I do not rule. as you well know.

260
00:24:28.926 --> 00:24:31.554
My father and I are mere
stewards of the King's will and wisdom.

261
00:24:31.637 --> 00:24:34.681
And how exactly
is that wisdom expressed...

262
00:24:35.015 --> 00:24:36.057
hm?

263
00:24:36.141 --> 00:24:39.102
In blinks and wheezes?

264
00:24:39.187 --> 00:24:40.873
I'd be surprised
if he could remember his own name.

265
00:24:40.897 --> 00:24:42.731
- Or if you could.
- King Viserys's condition

266
00:24:42.814 --> 00:24:45.317
- has worsened since you saw him last.
- Hah.

267
00:24:45.400 --> 00:24:48.112
It subjects him
to considerable pain.

268
00:24:48.196 --> 00:24:50.656
- On the advice of the maesters...
- Ah. the maesters.

269
00:24:50.739 --> 00:24:54.201
Of course.
It is they who keep him...

270
00:24:54.285 --> 00:24:55.452
addled on milk of the poppy

271
00:24:55.535 --> 00:24:58.080
while the High towers
warm his throne.

272
00:24:58.163 --> 00:25:00.082
Rhaenyra. if you would
see him without it.

273
00:25:00.166 --> 00:25:02.476
- almost blind with suffering.
- Oh. Alicent. I have no doubt

274
00:25:02.500 --> 00:25:05.713
it was... an act
of the purest mercy.

275
00:25:05.795 --> 00:25:08.216
but tell me.
for the King's suffering.

276
00:25:08.298 --> 00:25:09.633
did the maesters also prescribe

277
00:25:09.717 --> 00:25:11.427
the removal
of Targaryen heraldry

278
00:25:11.509 --> 00:25:15.180
and the installation
in its stead of various statues and stars?

279
00:25:15.264 --> 00:25:17.701
The emblems of the Seven serve
only to guide us on an uncertain path.

280
00:25:17.725 --> 00:25:21.437
- To remind us of a higher authority.
- And on the morrow.

281
00:25:21.519 --> 00:25:26.025
which authority will sit in judgment of
my son's claim on his own inheritance?

282
00:25:26.108 --> 00:25:28.777
- That would be mine... and the Hand's.
- Ah.

283
00:25:28.861 --> 00:25:30.821
But be assured.
the Father is just and commands me

284
00:25:30.862 --> 00:25:34.158
to forget the accusations
you have hurled in this room today.

285
00:25:40.331 --> 00:25:43.875
- Smaller than I remember.
- It looks exactly the same.

286
00:25:43.959 --> 00:25:46.920
Ah. Luke. come on.

287
00:26:00.726 --> 00:26:03.646
See? I told you this
would still be here.

288
00:26:03.728 --> 00:26:06.899
And you thought
you could swing Criston's morning star.

289
00:26:06.983 --> 00:26:08.900
And you almost took
your own head off.

290
00:26:14.532 --> 00:26:17.200
- What's your problem?
- Everyone's staring at us.

291
00:26:17.285 --> 00:26:18.326
Hyah!

292
00:26:20.579 --> 00:26:22.579
No one would question me
being heir to Driftmark...

293
00:26:24.166 --> 00:26:26.168
if...

294
00:26:26.252 --> 00:26:29.546
if I looked more like
Ser Laenor Velaryon than Ser Harwin Strong.

295
00:26:31.548 --> 00:26:33.967
It doesn't matter
what they think.

296
00:26:48.606 --> 00:26:50.109
Ooh.

297
00:27:18.763 --> 00:27:20.348
Well done. my Prince.

298
00:27:20.430 --> 00:27:21.782
You'll be winning
tourneys in no time.

299
00:27:21.806 --> 00:27:23.976
I don't give a shit
about tourneys.

300
00:27:24.810 --> 00:27:25.852
Nephews...

301
00:27:27.313 --> 00:27:29.564
have you come to train?

302
00:27:29.648 --> 00:27:31.025
Open the gate!

303
00:28:05.059 --> 00:28:06.779
Hold your nerve. my Queen.

304
00:28:06.852 --> 00:28:09.397
What we do.
we do for the good of the realm.

305
00:28:09.479 --> 00:28:14.192
I must confess
a certain uneasiness now this is at hand.

306
00:28:14.275 --> 00:28:18.531
- He may yet live.
- But we must be prepared if he does not.

307
00:28:26.871 --> 00:28:28.791
The realm has enjoyed
a long peace.

308
00:28:28.873 --> 00:28:31.794
a credit to the work
of both Jaehaerys and Viserys.

309
00:28:31.877 --> 00:28:36.465
but the threat of war looms
and may arrive on our shores.

310
00:28:36.548 --> 00:28:39.509
When it does.
will you want a child at the command

311
00:28:39.592 --> 00:28:41.804
of the greatest fleet
in Westeros?

312
00:28:43.639 --> 00:28:44.723
We must. of course...

313
00:28:46.600 --> 00:28:48.811
act in the interest
of our subjects.

314
00:28:50.896 --> 00:28:54.525
The next Lord of the Tides
will be deeply in your debt. Your Grace.

315
00:28:55.275 --> 00:28:56.776
As will Driftmark...

316
00:28:56.861 --> 00:28:58.903
in all its strength.

317
00:29:16.380 --> 00:29:17.756
Grandmother?

318
00:29:21.593 --> 00:29:24.596
Rhaena.

319
00:29:30.436 --> 00:29:31.812
Baela said you might be here.

320
00:29:33.647 --> 00:29:36.150
She's done well as your ward.

321
00:29:36.233 --> 00:29:37.525
You've. um...

322
00:29:38.902 --> 00:29:39.361
raised her admirably.

323
00:29:39.445 --> 00:29:43.698
You honor me. Princess.

324
00:29:43.782 --> 00:29:46.535
Might I speak to the Princess
alone. Rhaena?

325
00:29:49.871 --> 00:29:50.915
Princess.

326
00:30:00.716 --> 00:30:02.551
I wondered for many an hour

327
00:30:02.634 --> 00:30:06.263
what your purpose
was in coming here.

328
00:30:06.346 --> 00:30:09.390
Whether you'd speak for or against
the suit brought by Ser Vaemond.

329
00:30:09.475 --> 00:30:12.311
But then. I realized...

330
00:30:12.393 --> 00:30:14.313
you intend to advocate
for yourself.

331
00:30:17.650 --> 00:30:20.236
This is no fair proceeding.

332
00:30:20.319 --> 00:30:22.403
It is a trap

333
00:30:22.487 --> 00:30:24.406
set by the Queen and the Hand.
I'd wager.

334
00:30:24.489 --> 00:30:26.283
to proclaim my son illegitimate.

335
00:30:26.367 --> 00:30:29.327
Yet you did worse
than that with Laenor.

336
00:30:31.330 --> 00:30:32.665
Did you not?

337
00:30:39.004 --> 00:30:40.672
I loved your son.

338
00:30:42.967 --> 00:30:45.928
You may not believe it
to be true. but I did.

339
00:30:49.681 --> 00:30:51.808
I did not order his death.

340
00:30:54.311 --> 00:30:57.273
Nor was I complicit in it.
I swear this to you.

341
00:31:04.697 --> 00:31:06.156
I'll make you an offer.

342
00:31:09.701 --> 00:31:10.827
Back Luke's claim.

343
00:31:10.910 --> 00:31:13.663
and let us betroth
Laena's children to mine.

344
00:31:15.708 --> 00:31:20.211
Baela will be Queen
of the Seven Kingdoms

345
00:31:20.295 --> 00:31:22.965
and her sons will be
heirs to the throne.

346
00:31:23.047 --> 00:31:25.133
Rhaena will rule
in Driftmark. and...

347
00:31:25.217 --> 00:31:28.387
the seat will pass
to her and Lucerys's children in time.

348
00:31:28.469 --> 00:31:30.973
A generous offer.

349
00:31:33.057 --> 00:31:35.977
- Or a desperate one.
- What does it matter?

350
00:31:39.731 --> 00:31:42.610
You are right in this. at least.

351
00:31:46.863 --> 00:31:48.239
It does not matter.

352
00:31:57.833 --> 00:32:01.003
You can bargain
with me all you like.

353
00:32:01.085 --> 00:32:04.631
Bring my granddaughter
with you to soften my resolve.

354
00:32:06.132 --> 00:32:08.927
But tomorrow.
the High towers land their first blow.

355
00:32:11.346 --> 00:32:13.431
They force you to your knees...

356
00:32:13.515 --> 00:32:16.352
and I must stand alone.

357
00:32:59.727 --> 00:33:01.813
Alicent?

358
00:33:02.480 --> 00:33:04.065
Alicent...

359
00:33:04.149 --> 00:33:06.110
No. it's Rhaenyra. father.

360
00:33:10.363 --> 00:33:12.323
Rhaenyra.

361
00:33:18.121 --> 00:33:21.374
"The Song of Ice and Fire."
Do you believe it to be true?

362
00:33:24.169 --> 00:33:25.963
Aegon's Dream.

363
00:33:29.967 --> 00:33:31.552
You told me

364
00:33:31.634 --> 00:33:35.639
it was our duty to hold
the realm united against a common foe.

365
00:33:39.810 --> 00:33:42.729
By naming me heir.
you divided the realm.

366
00:33:52.864 --> 00:33:53.948
I thought I wanted it.

367
00:34:04.877 --> 00:34:07.004
But the burden is a heavy one.

368
00:34:08.756 --> 00:34:11.632
It's too heavy.

369
00:34:19.265 --> 00:34:20.350
My...

370
00:34:21.935 --> 00:34:23.102
My only child.

371
00:34:28.316 --> 00:34:31.277
If you wish me to bear it.
then defend me.

372
00:34:32.779 --> 00:34:34.323
And my children.

373
00:34:38.242 --> 00:34:41.287
It's...

374
00:35:35.843 --> 00:35:37.260
I want to have supper. Otto.

375
00:35:40.805 --> 00:35:44.267
- It is the morning. Your Grace.
- Tonight.

376
00:35:47.229 --> 00:35:49.898
The whole of my family...

377
00:35:49.981 --> 00:35:51.142
are gathered at the Red Keep.

378
00:35:54.485 --> 00:35:57.990
I want us... to dine together.

379
00:36:28.896 --> 00:36:30.981
Bring milk of the poppy.

380
00:36:45.329 --> 00:36:46.412
No.

381
00:36:48.789 --> 00:36:51.543
Just arrange the supper.

382
00:36:56.881 --> 00:36:58.717
Though it is the great
hope of this court

383
00:36:58.800 --> 00:37:03.137
that Lord Corlys Velaryon
survive his wounds.

384
00:37:03.222 --> 00:37:05.640
we gather here
with the grim task

385
00:37:05.724 --> 00:37:08.184
of dealing with
the succession of Driftmark.

386
00:37:09.436 --> 00:37:11.813
As Hand. I speak with
the King's voice on this

387
00:37:11.896 --> 00:37:14.231
and all other matters.

388
00:37:16.693 --> 00:37:18.612
The crown will now
hear the petitions.

389
00:37:19.863 --> 00:37:21.740
Ser Vaemond of House Velaryon.

390
00:37:29.956 --> 00:37:31.666
My Queen.

391
00:37:31.749 --> 00:37:33.793
My Lord Hand.

392
00:37:34.669 --> 00:37:36.380
The history of our noble houses

393
00:37:36.463 --> 00:37:38.048
extends beyond
the Seven Kingdoms

394
00:37:38.130 --> 00:37:40.300
to the days of Old Valyria.

395
00:37:40.383 --> 00:37:43.220
For as long
as House Targaryen has ruled the skies.

396
00:37:43.302 --> 00:37:45.889
House Velaryon
has ruled the seas.

397
00:37:45.972 --> 00:37:47.974
When the Doom fell on Valyria.

398
00:37:48.057 --> 00:37:50.601
our houses became
the last of their kind.

399
00:37:50.686 --> 00:37:52.080
Our forebearers
came to this new land.

400
00:37:52.104 --> 00:37:54.021
knowing that were they to fail.

401
00:37:54.106 --> 00:37:58.651
it would mean the end
to their bloodlines and their name.

402
00:37:58.735 --> 00:38:02.530
I have spent my entire life
on Driftmark defending my brother's seat.

403
00:38:02.613 --> 00:38:06.367
I am Lord Corlys's closest kin.
his own blood.

404
00:38:06.450 --> 00:38:10.497
The true. unimpeachable blood of
House Velaryon runs through my veins.

405
00:38:10.579 --> 00:38:14.543
As it does in my sons.
the offspring of Laenor Velaryon.

406
00:38:14.626 --> 00:38:17.378
If you cared so much
about your house's blood. Ser Vaemond.

407
00:38:17.461 --> 00:38:19.840
you would not be so bold as
to supplant its rightful heir.

408
00:38:19.923 --> 00:38:21.675
No. you only speak for yourself

409
00:38:21.758 --> 00:38:23.528
- and for your own ambition.
- You will have chance

410
00:38:23.552 --> 00:38:25.762
to make
your own petition. Princess Rhaenyra.

411
00:38:25.845 --> 00:38:28.432
Do Ser Vaemond
the courtesy of allowing his to be heard.

412
00:38:33.561 --> 00:38:37.064
What do you know
of Velaryon blood. Princess?

413
00:38:38.358 --> 00:38:41.403
I could cut my veins
and show it to you

414
00:38:41.485 --> 00:38:44.613
and you still
wouldn't recognize it.

415
00:38:44.697 --> 00:38:48.744
This is about the future
and survival of my house. not yours.

416
00:38:52.997 --> 00:38:56.084
My Queen. my Lord Hand.

417
00:38:57.126 --> 00:39:01.548
This is a matter of blood.
not ambition.

418
00:39:01.630 --> 00:39:05.427
I place the continuation of the survival
of my house and my line above all.

419
00:39:05.510 --> 00:39:10.682
I humbly put myself before you
as my brother's successor...

420
00:39:10.765 --> 00:39:14.269
the Lord of Driftmark
and Lord of the Tides.

421
00:39:15.436 --> 00:39:17.064
Thank you. Ser Vaemond.

422
00:39:23.195 --> 00:39:26.990
Princess Rhaenyra.
you may now speak

423
00:39:27.073 --> 00:39:29.492
for your son. Lucerys Velaryon.

424
00:39:34.956 --> 00:39:37.626
If I am to grace this farce
with some answer.

425
00:39:37.709 --> 00:39:40.749
I will start by reminding the court
that nearly 20 years ago. in this very...

426
00:39:46.550 --> 00:39:49.595
King Viserys of House Targaryen.

427
00:39:49.679 --> 00:39:51.597
the First of His Name.

428
00:39:51.680 --> 00:39:54.767
King of the Andals.
and the Rhoynar.

429
00:39:54.851 --> 00:39:57.104
and the First Men.

430
00:39:57.186 --> 00:40:02.441
Lord of the Seven Kingdoms.
and Protector of the Realm.

431
00:41:21.604 --> 00:41:23.481
I will sit the throne today.

432
00:41:25.441 --> 00:41:26.776
Your Grace.

433
00:41:33.992 --> 00:41:36.077
I will be fine.

434
00:41:50.675 --> 00:41:52.468
I said I'm fine.

435
00:41:55.972 --> 00:41:57.097
- Ah...
- Come on.

436
00:42:04.356 --> 00:42:06.816
Steady.

437
00:42:46.273 --> 00:42:52.695
I must... admit... my confusion.

438
00:42:54.280 --> 00:42:55.698
I do not understand

439
00:42:55.782 --> 00:43:00.160
why petitions are being heard
over a settled succession.

440
00:43:00.244 --> 00:43:03.456
The only one present...

441
00:43:03.539 --> 00:43:07.168
who might offer keener insight
into Lord Corlys's wishes

442
00:43:07.251 --> 00:43:09.921
is the Princess Rhaenys.

443
00:43:13.717 --> 00:43:15.343
Indeed. Your Grace.

444
00:43:29.231 --> 00:43:32.193
It was ever my husband's
will that Driftmark

445
00:43:32.276 --> 00:43:34.195
pass through Ser Laenor

446
00:43:34.278 --> 00:43:37.115
to his true born son...

447
00:43:37.948 --> 00:43:39.034
Lucerys Velaryon.

448
00:43:39.117 --> 00:43:42.746
His mind never changed.

449
00:43:42.829 --> 00:43:45.081
Nor did my support of him.

450
00:43:45.164 --> 00:43:48.418
As a matter of fact. the Princess
Rhaenyra has just informed me of her desire

451
00:43:48.501 --> 00:43:50.586
to marry her sons Jace and Luke

452
00:43:50.669 --> 00:43:55.383
to Lord Corlys's granddaughters.
Baela and Rhaena.

453
00:43:55.467 --> 00:43:59.387
A proposal to which
I heartily agree.

454
00:44:00.387 --> 00:44:04.017
Well... the matter is settled.

455
00:44:05.309 --> 00:44:06.602
Again.

456
00:44:07.896 --> 00:44:09.396
I hereby reaffirm

457
00:44:09.481 --> 00:44:12.275
Prince Lucerys of House Velaryon

458
00:44:12.358 --> 00:44:15.403
as heir to Driftmark.

459
00:44:15.487 --> 00:44:20.450
the Driftwood Throne.
and the next Lord of the Tides.

460
00:44:26.956 --> 00:44:28.499
You break law...

461
00:44:29.584 --> 00:44:31.418
and centuries of tradition

462
00:44:31.503 --> 00:44:33.630
to install your daughter
as heir.

463
00:44:35.673 --> 00:44:38.385
Yet you dare tell me...

464
00:44:38.468 --> 00:44:41.387
who deserves to inherit
the name Velaryon.

465
00:44:43.680 --> 00:44:46.059
No.

466
00:44:46.142 --> 00:44:48.394
I will not allow it.

467
00:44:49.019 --> 00:44:50.646
"Allow it"?

468
00:44:51.731 --> 00:44:53.900
Do not forget yourself. Vaemond.

469
00:44:57.737 --> 00:45:02.367
That is no true Velaryon.

470
00:45:02.450 --> 00:45:05.954
and certainly no nephew of mine.

471
00:45:06.037 --> 00:45:08.122
Go to your chambers.
You have said enough.

472
00:45:09.416 --> 00:45:12.876
Lucerys is
my true-born grandson.

473
00:45:13.878 --> 00:45:15.380
And you...

474
00:45:15.463 --> 00:45:16.630
are no more

475
00:45:16.713 --> 00:45:19.843
than the second son
of Driftmark.

476
00:45:19.925 --> 00:45:24.680
You... may run your house
as you see fit...

477
00:45:24.764 --> 00:45:28.726
but you will not decide
the future of mine.

478
00:45:30.602 --> 00:45:32.896
My house survived the Doom

479
00:45:32.981 --> 00:45:35.733
and a thousand
tribulations besides.

480
00:45:35.816 --> 00:45:37.651
And gods be damned...

481
00:45:38.945 --> 00:45:43.867
I will not see it ended
on the account of this...

482
00:45:46.202 --> 00:45:47.744
Say it.

483
00:45:58.298 --> 00:46:00.508
Her children...

484
00:46:00.592 --> 00:46:02.843
are bastards!

485
00:46:05.305 --> 00:46:07.557
And she...

486
00:46:08.432 --> 00:46:09.476
is...

487
00:46:10.267 --> 00:46:11.686
a whore.

488
00:46:18.151 --> 00:46:19.193
I...

489
00:46:20.987 --> 00:46:23.155
will have your tongue for that.

490
00:46:30.246 --> 00:46:31.539
He can keep his tongue.

491
00:46:31.622 --> 00:46:35.001
- Disarm him!
- No need.

492
00:46:41.798 --> 00:46:44.885
- Call the maesters!
- Father?

493
00:46:44.968 --> 00:46:47.764
Please. my love. You must
take something for the pain.

494
00:46:48.639 --> 00:46:50.390
I will not cloud my mind.

495
00:46:50.474 --> 00:46:52.851
I must put things right.

496
00:47:38.981 --> 00:47:43.610
The body will be ready for its return
to Driftmark on the morrow. my lady.

497
00:47:46.197 --> 00:47:50.284
You may wish to leave
the Silent Sisters to their work.

498
00:47:50.367 --> 00:47:52.829
It is ill luck to look
upon the face of death.

499
00:47:56.331 --> 00:48:00.919
The Stranger has visited me
more times than I can count. Grand Maester.

500
00:48:06.175 --> 00:48:08.720
I assure you...

501
00:48:08.802 --> 00:48:11.805
he cares little
whether my eyes are open or closed.

502
00:49:37.974 --> 00:49:41.396
How good it is...
to see you all tonight...

503
00:49:42.521 --> 00:49:43.814
together.

504
00:49:49.778 --> 00:49:53.740
- Prayer before we begin?
- Yes.

505
00:49:53.825 --> 00:49:56.202
May the Mother smile down
on this gathering with love.

506
00:49:56.284 --> 00:50:00.914
May the Smith mend the bonds
that have been broken for far too long.

507
00:50:00.997 --> 00:50:03.959
And to Vaemond Velaryon.
may the gods give him rest.

508
00:50:12.175 --> 00:50:16.012
This is an occasion
for celebration. it seems.

509
00:50:16.097 --> 00:50:18.557
My grandsons. Jace and Luke.

510
00:50:18.640 --> 00:50:21.936
will marry their cousins.
Baela and Rhaena.

511
00:50:22.019 --> 00:50:25.273
further strengthening the bond
between our houses.

512
00:50:25.356 --> 00:50:27.941
A toast to the young Princes...

513
00:50:28.025 --> 00:50:32.238
- and their betrothed.
- Hear. hear!

514
00:50:32.320 --> 00:50:35.782
Well done. Jace.
You'll finally get to lie with a woman.

515
00:50:35.867 --> 00:50:40.371
Let us toast as well
Prince Lucerys...

516
00:50:40.454 --> 00:50:43.291
the future Lord of the Tides.

517
00:50:43.374 --> 00:50:44.459
Hear. hear.

518
00:50:44.541 --> 00:50:46.168
You'll be great.

519
00:50:49.880 --> 00:50:54.218
You do know how the act
is done. I assume?

520
00:50:54.302 --> 00:50:55.427
At least in principle?

521
00:50:55.510 --> 00:50:56.929
Where to put your cock
and all that.

522
00:50:57.012 --> 00:50:58.389
Let it be. cousin.

523
00:50:58.472 --> 00:50:59.615
You can play the jester
if you wish.

524
00:50:59.639 --> 00:51:03.269
- but hold your tongue before my betrothed.
- Mm-hm.

525
00:51:23.747 --> 00:51:28.293
It both gladdens my heart

526
00:51:28.376 --> 00:51:32.506
and fills me with sorrow

527
00:51:32.590 --> 00:51:35.802
to see these faces
around the table.

528
00:51:36.927 --> 00:51:40.722
The faces most dear
to me in all the world...

529
00:51:42.182 --> 00:51:44.476
yet grown so distant
from each other...

530
00:51:45.061 --> 00:51:47.521
in the years past.

531
00:52:10.503 --> 00:52:13.923
My own face...

532
00:52:14.005 --> 00:52:16.300
is no longer a handsome one...

533
00:52:19.052 --> 00:52:20.137
if indeed it ever was.

534
00:52:24.267 --> 00:52:26.309
But tonight...

535
00:52:26.394 --> 00:52:29.771
I wish you to see me... as I am.

536
00:52:31.189 --> 00:52:32.775
Not just a king...

537
00:52:34.485 --> 00:52:37.363
but your father.

538
00:52:37.445 --> 00:52:38.655
Your brother.

539
00:52:39.322 --> 00:52:40.950
Your husband...

540
00:52:43.285 --> 00:52:44.912
and your grand sire.

541
00:52:45.912 --> 00:52:48.081
Who may not. it seems...

542
00:52:49.083 --> 00:52:50.959
walk for much longer among you.

543
00:52:56.798 --> 00:53:01.345
Let us no longer hold
ill feelings in our hearts.

544
00:53:02.637 --> 00:53:04.264
The crown cannot stand strong

545
00:53:04.347 --> 00:53:07.017
if the House of the Dragon
remains divided.

546
00:53:07.851 --> 00:53:10.771
But set aside your grievances.

547
00:53:14.150 --> 00:53:16.318
If not for the sake
of the crown...

548
00:53:17.403 --> 00:53:19.572
then for the sake
of this old man

549
00:53:20.155 --> 00:53:23.075
who loves you all

550
00:53:23.159 --> 00:53:24.744
so dearly.

551
00:53:51.686 --> 00:53:54.773
I wish to raise my cup
to Her Grace. the Queen.

552
00:53:58.735 --> 00:54:01.155
I love my father.

553
00:54:01.238 --> 00:54:04.742
But I must admit
that no one has stood...

554
00:54:04.825 --> 00:54:07.410
more loyally by his side
than his good wife.

555
00:54:10.539 --> 00:54:12.416
She has tended to him with...

556
00:54:13.584 --> 00:54:15.628
unfailing devotion.

557
00:54:15.711 --> 00:54:18.255
love. and honor.

558
00:54:19.715 --> 00:54:22.175
And for that.
she has my gratitude...

559
00:54:24.095 --> 00:54:25.680
and my apology.

560
00:54:35.021 --> 00:54:37.900
Your graciousness
moves me deeply. Princess.

561
00:54:41.195 --> 00:54:43.072
We are both mothers...

562
00:54:45.490 --> 00:54:47.367
and we love our children.

563
00:54:50.787 --> 00:54:53.708
We have more in common
than we sometimes allow.

564
00:54:56.961 --> 00:55:00.423
I raise my cup to you...
and to your house.

565
00:55:05.510 --> 00:55:07.470
You will make a fine queen.

566
00:55:43.506 --> 00:55:45.468
I. um...

567
00:55:45.550 --> 00:55:49.055
I regret the disappointment
you are soon to suffer.

568
00:55:49.137 --> 00:55:52.599
But if you ever wish to know
what it is to be well satisfied.

569
00:55:52.682 --> 00:55:54.726
all you have to do is ask.

570
00:55:55.436 --> 00:55:58.104
Jace.

571
00:56:24.215 --> 00:56:29.177
To Prince Aegon and...
Prince Aemond.

572
00:56:29.260 --> 00:56:32.639
We have not seen
each other in years.

573
00:56:32.722 --> 00:56:35.476
but I have fond memories
of our shared youth.

574
00:56:37.894 --> 00:56:42.858
And as men. I hope we may
yet be friends and allies.

575
00:56:42.941 --> 00:56:45.485
To you and your family's
good health. dear uncles.

576
00:56:53.494 --> 00:56:54.744
To you as well.

577
00:57:01.501 --> 00:57:03.921
Beware the beast beneath the boards.

578
00:57:04.003 --> 00:57:05.421
Well done. my boy.

579
00:57:05.505 --> 00:57:09.802
I would like to toast
to Baela and Rhaena.

580
00:57:09.885 --> 00:57:12.762
They'll be married soon.

581
00:57:12.847 --> 00:57:16.057
It isn't so bad.
Mostly he just ignores you...

582
00:57:17.101 --> 00:57:19.186
except sometimes
when he's drunk.

583
00:57:27.610 --> 00:57:30.990
- Good.
- Let us have some music.

584
00:57:36.327 --> 00:57:37.537
Excuse me.

585
00:59:08.378 --> 00:59:11.881
Guards.

586
00:59:19.014 --> 00:59:20.557
Please. sit down.

587
00:59:59.470 --> 01:00:01.432
Final tribute.

588
01:00:04.309 --> 01:00:06.436
To the health of my nephews:

589
01:00:07.271 --> 01:00:08.981
Jace...

590
01:00:09.064 --> 01:00:11.150
Luke...

591
01:00:12.108 --> 01:00:13.401
and Joffrey.

592
01:00:14.820 --> 01:00:18.197
Each of them handsome. wise...

593
01:00:22.827 --> 01:00:25.247
hm...

594
01:00:25.331 --> 01:00:26.874
- strong.
- Aemond.

595
01:00:26.956 --> 01:00:28.041
Come...

596
01:00:29.668 --> 01:00:33.963
let us drain our cups
to these three...

597
01:00:34.048 --> 01:00:35.441
- Strong boys.
- I dare you to say that again.

598
01:00:35.465 --> 01:00:39.345
Why? 'Twas only a compliment.

599
01:00:39.427 --> 01:00:41.555
Do you not think
yourself Strong?

600
01:00:41.637 --> 01:00:43.765
- Jace!
- That is enough!

601
01:00:50.104 --> 01:00:51.874
Why would you
say such a thing before these people?

602
01:00:51.898 --> 01:00:55.903
I was merely expressing
how proud I am of my family. Mother.

603
01:00:55.985 --> 01:00:59.865
Mm. though it seems
my nephews aren't quite as proud of theirs.

604
01:00:59.947 --> 01:01:01.784
Wait. wait!

605
01:01:05.412 --> 01:01:07.664
Go to your quarters.
All of you go. now.

606
01:01:19.675 --> 01:01:22.679
Mm.

607
01:01:27.267 --> 01:01:30.311
Rhaenyra.

608
01:01:32.856 --> 01:01:35.526
It's best. I think. if we
go back to Dragons tone.

609
01:01:35.608 --> 01:01:36.693
You've only just arrived.

610
01:01:43.534 --> 01:01:44.700
Let me see the children home.

611
01:01:46.369 --> 01:01:47.704
I'll. um...

612
01:01:48.372 --> 01:01:50.916
return on dragon back.

613
01:01:55.378 --> 01:01:57.296
The King and I
would both like that.

614
01:02:39.005 --> 01:02:42.258
It's been quite a night
at the castle. it seems.

615
01:02:43.552 --> 01:02:45.095
Yes. my lady.

616
01:03:19.921 --> 01:03:21.756
Come on. come on.

617
01:03:25.468 --> 01:03:27.887
That's it.

618
01:03:36.979 --> 01:03:38.023
Oh...

619
01:03:39.358 --> 01:03:40.651
Well done.

620
01:03:47.490 --> 01:03:49.659
- I'm sorry.
- Shh.

621
01:03:49.742 --> 01:03:51.869
- I'm sorry.
- Shh. shh. shh.

622
01:03:54.372 --> 01:03:56.249
But you wanted to know...

623
01:03:57.334 --> 01:03:59.418
if I believe it to be true.

624
01:04:01.338 --> 01:04:03.215
Believe what to be true.
my King?

625
01:04:04.173 --> 01:04:05.800
Don't you remember?

626
01:04:07.552 --> 01:04:10.597
Aegon...

627
01:04:11.347 --> 01:04:14.392
Our son?

628
01:04:14.851 --> 01:04:16.936
His Dream.

629
01:04:17.019 --> 01:04:18.146
The Song of Ice...

630
01:04:18.229 --> 01:04:20.273
and Fi...

631
01:04:21.566 --> 01:04:23.151
It is true.

632
01:04:24.193 --> 01:04:26.070
What he saw in the North.

633
01:04:27.738 --> 01:04:29.865
The Prince That Was Promised.

634
01:04:31.742 --> 01:04:33.119
I don't understand. Viserys.

635
01:04:33.202 --> 01:04:35.289
The Prince.

636
01:04:35.372 --> 01:04:36.914
Prince Aegon?

637
01:04:39.126 --> 01:04:40.793
To unite the realm

638
01:04:40.876 --> 01:04:44.046
against the cold...
and the dark.

639
01:04:47.843 --> 01:04:49.427
It is you.

640
01:04:52.222 --> 01:04:55.267
You are the one.

641
01:04:55.767 --> 01:04:56.851
You must do this.

642
01:04:58.561 --> 01:05:01.439
You must do this.

643
01:05:21.626 --> 01:05:23.211
Shh. shh.

644
01:05:46.068 --> 01:05:47.903
I understand. my King.

645
01:06:08.298 --> 01:06:10.425
No more.

646
01:06:10.508 --> 01:06:12.093
No more.

647
01:06:40.872 --> 01:06:41.872
My love.
